title: Defence secretary meets family of Kenyan woman allegedly killed by British soldiers
description: Relatives of Agnes Wanjiru say 13-year fight for justice has taken ‘heavy toll’ after meeting with John HealeyThe family of a Kenyan woman who was allegedly killed by British soldiers have said their 13-year fight for justice has taken a “heavy toll”, and that they have been offered “too many empty promises” after a meeting with the defence secretary.Agnes Wanjiru was 21 when she disappeared in March 2012. She was last seen in the company of British soldiers in a bar in a hotel in Nanyuki, a town in eastern Kenya where the British army has a military base, BATUK. Continue reading...
author: Hannah Al-Othman North of England correspondent

title: Trump administration revokes all South Sudanese visas in repatriation row
description: State department accuses east African country of ‘taking advantage of the United States’The US is revoking the visas of all South Sudanese passport-holders and will stop any more of its citizens entering the country.The Department of State said South Sudan was “taking advantage of the United States” by failing to comply with US efforts to return people to the east African country, adding that the measures would come into effect immediately. title: Pentagon says US will help Panama take back canal from Chinese influence
description: US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth visited Panama. He promised collaboration to curb China's influence on the Panama Canal. Hegseth's visit marks growing US concerns about Chinese projects in the region. Former President Trump suggested military force to reclaim the canal. President Jose Raul Mulino supports US efforts. He pulled Panama out of China's Belt and Road Initiative.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Dominican nightclub roof collapses during concert, killing 66: What we know so far
description: A tragic incident occurred in Santo Domingo. The Jet Set nightclub's roof collapsed during a merengue concert. Sixty-six people died and over 160 sustained injuries. Rescue teams are searching for more survivors. Octavio Dotel and Tony Blanco, former baseball players, are among the dead. Nelsy Cruz, a governor, also died. The cause of the collapse is under investigation.
author: TOI World Desk
